        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: add inbound peer send policy matching",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds native `session.sendPolicy.rules[].match.peerEquals: \"inboundPeer\"` support.\n- Allows relational send-policy checks between the outbound target and the inbound peer for the current turn, including identityLinks aliases.\n- Threads inbound peer context through automatic replies, routed replies, explicit `message.send`, plugin/gateway message-action delivery, and durable outbound delivery.\n- Keeps send-policy-only predicates out of shared allow/deny scopes.\n- Reports blocked durable sends as `denied_by_send_policy` suppression outcomes and returns suppressed explicit sends without calling transport.\n- Adds focused unit coverage and docs/help labels for the new predicate.\n\nFixes #85175.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm test src/sessions/send-policy.test.ts src/config/schema.hints.test.ts src/cli/config-cli.test.ts src/infra/outbound/message.test.ts src/infra/outbound/outbound-send-service.test.ts src/agents/tools/message-tool.test.ts src/infra/outbound/message-action-runner.plugin-dispatch.test.ts`\n- `pnpm check:changed`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: `sendPolicy` can now allow same-peer delivery and suppress wrong-peer outbound delivery when `peerEquals: \"inboundPeer\"` is configured.\n\nReal environment tested: local OpenClaw source checkout on Linux, branch `fix/send-policy-peer-equals-inbound-peer`, commit `f329ecb842`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: ran the focused test command above and `pnpm check:changed` after commit `f329ecb842`. Also ran a local terminal smoke against the after-fix send-policy resolver with redacted Telegram-like peer ids.\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\nTerminal capture from the focused run:\n\n```text\n[test] passed 5 Vitest shards in 32.58s\n```\n\nTerminal capture from `pnpm check:changed`:\n\n```text\n[check:changed] typecheck core\n[check:changed] typecheck core tests\n[check:changed] lint core\nruntime-sidecar-loaders: local runtime sidecar loaders look OK.\nImport cycle check: 0 runtime value cycle(s).\n```\n\nThe new tests cover same-peer allow, wrong-peer denial metadata, missing inbound peer behavior, identityLinks alias comparison, schema split rejection for shared scopes, explicit `message.send` inboundPeer propagation, message tool propagation, and message-action send-policy suppression before gateway/plugin delivery.\n\nObserved result after fix: same-peer configured sends are allowed when the outbound target equals a trusted inbound peer candidate; wrong-peer sends are denied/suppressed before transport with `send_policy_peer_mismatch` / `denied_by_send_policy` metadata. Focused tests passed and `pnpm check:changed` completed successfully.\n\nWhat was not tested: no private Telegram credentials, IPs, phone numbers, API keys, or non-public endpoints are included here. Live Telegram proof was requested from Mantis in PR comment https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/85763#issuecomment-4526509925; if it posts provider proof, it can be appended as stronger external evidence.\n",
        "branch": "fix/send-policy-peer-equals-inbound-peer",
